    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"439483\">Andrew Yang</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.60fg_of_localized_maximal.60.20for.20semi-local.20ring/near/515696522\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I am fairly certain we don't. The closest we have is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Module.Finite.of_localizationSpan%27#doc\">docs#Module.Finite.of_localizationSpan'</a> but I don't think this is useful here.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thanks! I’ll try to formalize this. It actually will be used to show that if a semi-local domain  <code>A</code> is locally a PID at each of its maximal ideals, then <code>A</code> itself is a PID—first by establishing that <code>A</code> is Noetherian.</p>",
