        "sender_full_name": "Yiming Fu",
        "timestamp": 1746244770
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We do have this though:<br>\n<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsPrincipalIdealRing.of_finite_primes#doc\">docs#IsPrincipalIdealRing.of_finite_primes</a></p>",
        "id": 515866099,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1746259494
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks—I found that theorem as well. In fact, for the original problem we’ve already shown that if <code>A</code> is Noetherian then it’s a Dedekind domain (then we can apply <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsPrincipalIdealRing.of_finite_primes#doc\">docs#IsPrincipalIdealRing.of_finite_primes</a>), so it now remains only to prove this lemma.</p>",
